WHAT THIS MEANS FOR THE AERO-RESEARCH-PLATFORM
-----------------------------------------------

Every surrogate trained on this dataset is itself a derivative work and
inherits the CC-BY-NC-4.0 obligation. The platform's CertificateOfValidity
framework codifies this:

  * The `non_commercial` flag is auto-set to True on any cert tied to a
    training run that touched DrivAerNet++.
  * The flag is write-once-True — once set, it cannot be reset to False
    via model_copy (the certificate.py model_copy override blocks this).
  * The surrogate_name carries a forced `_nc` suffix so every artifact,
    MLflow run, and directory listing visually signals the obligation.
  * The cert's `attribution_required` field records the citation strings
    every publication/demo/blog post MUST carry.
  * The `.github/workflows/non-commercial-fence.yml` CI workflow rejects
    any code that imports the quarantined loader without producing
    `non_commercial=True` or the `# non-commercial: justified` pragma.
  * The `.github/workflows/license-audit.yml` CI workflow scans new
    artifacts and PR diffs for cross-license contamination.


CITATION
--------

Any publication, presentation, or public artifact that uses DrivAerNet++
or anything derived from it MUST cite:

  Elrefaie, M., Morar, F., Dai, A., & Ahmed, F. (2024).
  DrivAerNet++: A Large-Scale Multimodal Car Dataset with Computational
  Fluid Dynamics Simulations and Deep Learning Benchmarks.
  In Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems
  (NeurIPS Datasets & Benchmarks Track).

  arXiv: 2406.09624
  Dataverse: https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataverse/DrivAerNet

The aero-research-platform's `attribution_required` cert field carries
this citation automatically; the MLflow tag captures it on every run.


COMMERCIAL USE EXCEPTION
------------------------

If your use case drifts into commercial territory (paid consulting,
product engineering, monetised hosting of trained weights, etc.) you
MUST either:

  1. Retrain on CC-BY-SA-only datasets (AhmedML, WindsorML, DrivAerML)
     and issue a fresh cert with `non_commercial=False`, OR
  2. Contact the dataset authors (https://github.com/Mohamedelrefaie/DrivAerNet)
     for an explicit commercial-use waiver in writing.

The platform's structural defences will refuse to invoke a
`non_commercial=True` cert from a context flagged commercial; do not
attempt to bypass them.
